1651/http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/n1/nantasket.htm |url-status=dead |archive-date=15 March 2004 |title=Nantasket |website=[[Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships]] |publisher=[[United States Navy]] |accessdate=12 December 2013 }}</ref>\n* 1868: {{USS|Alaska|1868|6}} ([[sloop of war]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/a5/alaska-i.htm |title=Alaska |website=[[Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships]] |publisher=[[United States Navy]] |accessdate=12 December 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120302232157/http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/a5/alaska-i.htm |archivedate=2 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> [[Battle of Ganghwa]]\n* 1876: {{USS|Vandalia|1876|6}} ([[sloop of war]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/v1/vandalia-ii.htm |title=Vandalia |website=[[Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships]] |publisher=[[United States Navy]] |accessdate=12 December 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213094654/http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/v1/vandalia-ii.htm |archivedate=13 December 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> [[1889 Apia cyclone]]\n* 1916: {{USS|Bridge|AF-1|6}} ([[Combat stores ship]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/b9/bridge-i.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060724044811/http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/b9/bridge-i.htm |url-status=dead |archive-date=24 July 2006 |title=Bridge |website=[[Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships]] |publisher=[[United States Navy]] |accessdate=14 December 2013 }}</ref> [[World War I]]; [[World War II]]\n* 1919: {{USS|Brazos|AO-4|6}} ([[Fleet oiler]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hazegray.org/danfs/auxil/ao4.htm |title=Brazos |website=[[Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships]] |publisher=[[United States Navy]] |accessdate=14 December 2013}}</ref> [[World War II]]\n* 1920: {{USS|Neches|AO-5|6}} ([[Fleet oiler]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/n3/neches-i.htm |arch