ates Navy]] |accessdate=12 December 2013 }}</ref>\n* 1866: {{USS|Worcester|1866|6}} ([[sloop of war]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/w11/worcester-i.htm |title=Worcester |website=[[Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships]] |publisher=[[United States Navy]] |accessdate=12 December 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213023800/http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/w11/worcester-i.htm |archivedate=13 December 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n* 1867: {{USS|Nantasket|1867|6}} ([[sloop of war]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/n1/nantasket.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040315181651/http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/n1/nantasket.htm |url-status=dead |archive-date=15 March 2004 |title=Nantasket |website=[[Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships]] |publisher=[[United States Navy]] |accessdate=12 December 2013 }}</ref>\n* 1868: {{USS|Alaska|1868|6}} ([[sloop of war]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/a5/alaska-i.htm |title=Alaska |website=[[Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships]] |publisher=[[United States Navy]] |accessdate=12 December 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120302232157/http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/a5/alaska-i.htm |archivedate=2 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> [[Battle of Ganghwa]]\n* 1876: {{USS|Vandalia|1876|6}} ([[sloop of war]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/v1/vandalia-ii.htm |title=Vandalia |website=[[Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships]] |publisher=[[United States Navy]] |accessdate=12 December 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213094654/http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/v1/vandalia-ii.htm |archivedate=13 December 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> [[1889 Apia cyclone]]\n* 1916: {{USS|Bridge|AF-1|6}} ([[Combat stores ship]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/b9/bridge-i.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060724044811/h