4\u201345)|Philippines campaign]]; [[Battle of Iwo Jima]]; [[Battle of Okinawa]]\n* 1943: {{USS|Haraden|DD-585}} ([[Fletcher-class destroyer|''Fletcher''-class destroyer]])<ref name=\"silverstone140\"/> [[Philippines Campaign (1944\u201345)|Philippines campaign]]\n* 1943: {{USS|Newcomb|DD-586}} ([[Fletcher-class destroyer|''Fletcher''-class destroyer]])<ref name=\"silverstone140\"/> [[Battle of Surigao Strait]]; [[Battle of Iwo Jima]]; [[Battle of Okinawa]]\n* 1943: {{USS|Bennion|DD-662}} ([[Fletcher-class destroyer|''Fletcher''-class destroyer]])<ref name=\"silverstone141\">Silverstone, Paul H. ''U.S. Warships of World War II'' (1968) Doubleday & Company p.141</ref> [[Battle of Leyte]]; [[Battle of Iwo Jima]]; [[Battle of Okinawa]]\n* 1943: {{USS|Heywood L. Edwards|DD-663}} ([[Fletcher-class destroyer|''Fletcher''-class destroyer]])<ref name=\"silverstone141\"/> [[Battle of Surigao Strait]]; [[Battle of Iwo Jima]]; [[Battle of Okinawa]]\n* 1943: {{USS|Richard P. Leary|DD-664}} ([[Fletcher-class destroyer|''Fletcher''-class destroyer]])<ref name=\"silverstone141\"/> [[Battle of Surigao Strait]]; [[Battle of Iwo Jima]]; [[Battle of Okinawa]]\n* 1942: HMS {{HMS|Bayntun|K310|2}} ([[Captain-class frigate]])<ref name=\"lenton\">Lenton, H.T. & Colledge, J.J. (1968) ''British and Dominion Warships of World War II'' Doubleday pp.242\u2013245</ref> shared credit for sinking [[German submarine U-757|''U-757'']], [[German submarine U-1279|''U-1279'']], [[German submarine U-989|''U-989'']] & [[German submarine U-1278|''U-1278'']]\n* 1942: HMS {{HMS|Bazely|K311|2}} ([[Captain-class frigate]])<ref name=\"lenton\"/> shared credit for sinking [[German submarine U-648|''U-648'']], [[German submarine U-600|''U-600'']] & [[German submarine U-636|''U-636'']]\n* 1942: HMS {{HMS|Berry|K312|2}} ([[Captain-class frigate]])<ref name=\"lenton\"/> [[Battle of the Atlantic]]\n* 1942: HMS {{HMS|Blackwood|K313|2}} ([[Captain-class frigate]])<ref name=\"lenton\"/> shared credit for sinking [[German submarine U-648|''U-648'']] & [[German submarine U-600|''U-600'']]\n* 1942: {{USS|Evarts|DE-5}} ([[Evarts-class destroyer escort|''Evarts''-class destroyer escort]])<ref name=\"silverstone153\">Silverstone, Paul H. ''U.S. Warships of World War II'' (1968) Doubleday & Company p.153</ref> [[Battle of the Atlantic]]\n* 1942: {{USS|Wyffels|DE-6}} ([[Evarts-class destroyer escort|''Evarts''-class destroyer escort]])<ref name=\"silverstone153\"/> [[Battle of the Atlantic]]\n* 1943: {{USS|Griswold|DE-7}} ([[Evarts-class destroyer escort|''Evarts''-class destroyer escort]])<ref name=\"silverstone153\"/> shared credit for sinking {{Ship|Japanese submarine|I-39||2}}; [[Battle of Okinawa]]\n* 1943: {{USS|Steele|DE-8}} ([[Evarts-class destroyer escort|''Evarts''-class destroyer escort]])<ref name=\"silverstone153\"/> [[Asiatic-Pacific Theater|Pacific Theater of Operations]]\n* 1943: {{USS|Carlson|DE-9}} ([[Evarts-class destroyer escort|''Evarts''-class destroyer escort]])<ref name=\"silverstone153\"/> [[Battle of Okinawa]]\n* 1943: {{USS|Bebas|DE-10}} ([[Evarts-class destroyer escort|''Evarts''-class destroyer escort]])<ref name=\"silverstone155\"/> [[Battle of Okinawa]]\n* 1943: {{USS|Crouter|DE-11}} ([[Evarts-class destroyer escort|''Evarts''-class destroyer escort]])<ref name=\"silverstone155\">Silverstone, Paul H. ''U.S. Warships of World War II'' (1968) Doubleday & Company p.155</ref> [[Battle of Okinawa]]\n* 1943: HMS {{HMS|Burges|K347|2}} ([[Captain-class frigate]])<ref name=\"lenton\"/> shared credit for sinking [[German submarine U-1063|''U-1063'']]\n* 1943: {{USS|Seid|DE-256}} ([[Evarts-class destroyer escort|''Evarts''-class destroyer escort]])<ref name=\"silverstone155\"/> [[Battle of Okinawa]]\n* 1943: {{USS|Smartt|DE-257}} ([[Evarts-class destroyer escort|''Evarts''-class destroyer escort]])<ref name=\"silverstone155\"/> [[Battle of the Atlantic]]\n* 1943: {{USS|Walter S. Brown|DE-258}} ([[Evarts-class destroyer escort|''Evarts''-class destroyer escort]])<ref n